Italy - Epizootic hemorrhagic disease virus
-------------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Started: 24 Oct 2022
Confirmed: 13 Nov 2022
Reported: 17 Nov 2022
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence in a zone or a compartment
Causal agent: Epizootic haemorrhagic disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Trapani, Sicily
Started: 24 Oct 2022
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 32 / 3 / 1 / - / - / -

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Control measures at event level, domestic animals: Vector surveillance, traceability, surveillance within the restricted zone, surveillance outside the restricted zone, screening, movement control, control of wildlife reservoirs, control of vectors

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Reference Laboratory for exotic animal diseases / Cattle / Real-time reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction (rRT-PCR) / 13 Nov 2022 / Positive

