Communicated by:
ProMED

[Italy suffers at present 2 primary disease events in cattle caused by EHD virus. Its 1st reported outbreaks were from Sardinia (3 locations in the west of South Sardinia; 20221110.8706660 and WOAH immediate notification at https://wahis.woah.org/#/in-review/4712). The start dates of the events presented in the 2 WOAH reports are 28 Oct 2022 for Sardinia and 24 Oct 2022 for Sicily. In case these dates are accurate, such synchronicity might be attributed to weather conditions, allowing airborne transmission of infected (_Culicoides_) vectors from north Africa. The distances between the affected locations in Sardinia and Sicily from Tunisia are about 280 and 200 km (174 mi and 124 mi), respectively.

The EHD virus causing the outbreak in Tunisia during October-November 2021 has been recently published to be serotype 8. The serotyping of the current outbreaks in Tunisia, Sardinia and Sicily is pending.

EU member-states and some non-members have been applying vaccination against circulating bluetongue virus, a vector-borne orbivirus of domestic ruminants, using an inactivated vaccine against the relevant serotype, since the extensive BTV-8 event. Similar policy may be considered in relation to EHD. At present, no licensed vaccine against EHD in cattle is commercially available. - Mod.AS

